<HEADLINE>
<P>
ELVIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How ironic for Priscilla to say, " 'We are into preserving Elvis' name and 
image,' " when she published her book exposing Elvis' most intimate moments and 
then co-produced the TV miniseries aimed at eroding his reputation. If she felt 
"a cultural responsibility," she would handle his image with more taste. The 
love that existed between Elvis and his public has been destroyed by this 
crassness. 
</P>
<P>
S. FRANCIS 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
