<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE GODDESS THEORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regardless of the academic validity of Marija Gimbutas' studies, a case can be 
made for the benefits of a female ruler of a culture ("The Goddess Theory," by 
Jacques Leslie, June 11). The female, as carrier of future generations, would 
be more concerned with promoting a peaceful environment. Perhaps this kind of 
thinking may lead some brave women to become presidential candidates. It's 
about time. 
</P>
<P>
LINDA UMSTEAD 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
