<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MESSAGE OF 'DO THE RIGHT THING' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Jewish Defense Organization is wrong to call for a boycott against "Do the 
Right Thing" (as reported in Steve Hochman's July 16 article, "The Aftermath of 
Public Enemy's Collapse"). 
</P>
<P>
Spike Lee's movie has a powerful message for all of society -- that all 
Americans should strive to understand one another in order to live together 
without hatred and violence. 
</P>
<P>
Maybe the JDO should encourage viewing of the film in an effort to combat 
anti-Semitic prejudice such as that expressed by Prof. Griff of Public Enemy, 
the rap group that Hochman wrote about. 
</P>
<P>
ELIZABETH ANNE 
</P>
<P>
BAGASAO 
</P>
