<HEADLINE>
<P>
LATINO THEATER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a Latina actress, I read with interest the views of Jose Armand on Latin 
theater in Los Angeles ("Paving the Way for Festival Latino," by Douglas 
Sadownick, July 9). However, I was dismayed at his comment that the Bilingual 
Foundation for the Arts is the only group that offers Latin theater on a 
regular basis. 
</P>
<P>
I am part of a theater ensemble named Sinergia and am appearing in an 
all-Spanish play, "Una Familia Tipo" ("A Family Type"), directed by Anibal 
Aprile, who last year won a Cesar Award for his play "Entre Las Redes" ("Caught 
in a Web"). The Cesar Award is presented to Latin theater actors, directors, 
authors, etc., by the Panamerican Theatrical Assn. 
</P>
<P>
I point out the Cesar Awards to Mr. Armand, who said in his interview that 
"there's no Latino theater award. . . . " 
</P>
<P>
TINA D'MARCO 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
