<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEIL AND BRUCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In regard to Daniel Paul's July 9 letter stating that if it hadn't been for 
Neil Diamond the world would not have Bruce Springsteen's song "Born in the 
U.S.A." or the movie "Yentl": 
</P>
<P>
I find it unacceptable to think Mr. Springsteen had Neil Diamond anywhere on 
his mind while writing "Born in the U.S.A." just because America and U.S.A. are 
synonymous. 
</P>
<P>
The only similarities I can see between "Yentl" and the film "The Jazz Singer" 
is that both of their characters were Jewish. 
</P>
<P>
I have nothing against Neil Diamond. I am simply against the belief that Neil 
Diamond is God. 
</P>
<P>
SEAN TUCKER 
</P>
<P>
Bakersfield 
