<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEIL AND BRUCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is a laughable assertion that Bruce Springsteen would never have written 
"Born in the U.S.A.," about a bitter and disenfranchised Vietnam veteran, 
without the precedent of Neil Diamond's "America," an anthem so jingoistic it 
could be inscribed on the Statue of Liberty. 
</P>
<P>
Perhaps the myopic Mr. Paul derived his understanding of Springsteen's song 
from Ronald Reagan, who had obviously had heard only the title when he let the 
song be used in his '84 campaign. 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM BROUGH 
