<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOUTH BEAT: YMCAS OFFER SPECIAL PACKAGES IN SEVERAL CITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LUCY IZON, Izon is a Canadian travel journalist covering youth budget 
routes. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Young travelers on tight budgets who prefer avoiding the restrictive hours and 
lack of privacy usually associated with youth hostels can investigate the 
YMCA's international network of budget lodgings. 
</P>
<P>
This year the association has added new, low-cost "do-it-yourself" tour 
packages for Washington, D.C., and a newly affiliated hotel in Bangkok, 
Thailand. 
</P>
<P>
Details about accommodation prices and facilities at Ys in North America, 
Western Europe, the Far East and the South Pacific are available through a 
special "Ys Way" brochure produced by the YMCA of Greater New York. 
</P>
<P>
The 103 facilities listed include Ys and affiliated budget accommodations. Most 
provide lodgings for men and women at an average rate of $24 per person a night 
for single or twin rooms. 
</P>
<P>
One of the advantages of the "Ys Way" program is that you can reserve budget 
accommodations before you go. 
</P>
<P>
Not all of the locations listed are YMCAs. In some areas the association has 
made arrangements to include suitable alternative lodging, such as hotels that 
cater to a young clientele. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Near Swiss Ski Areas 
</P>
<P>
In Switzerland, for example, the "Ys Way" program lists various S.S.R. Hotels 
operated by Switzerland's National Student Travel Service. Most are within easy 
reach of popular ski areas, and some offer accommodations during the summer. 
</P>
<P>
A recent addition to the international network is the Collins House 
International Y at 27 S. Sathorn Road in Bangkok. It offers 147 rooms at $25 
U.S. single or $30 twin a night. The hotel also has a fitness center, jogging 
track, swimming pool, restaurant, bar and massage room. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to accommodations, the program offers travel packages in New York 
City, New Orleans, Los Angeles (including Hollywood), Seattle and Washington, 
D.C. for independent travelers. 
</P>
<P>
Packages are two to five nights and include accommodations in single or twin 
rooms, breakfasts, several other meals and tickets for local tours. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Smithsonian Museums 
</P>
<P>
The new Washington packages are from two to four nights and offer 
accommodations at the Hotel Harrington four blocks from the White House. It is 
also within walking distance of the free Smithsonian museums and just one block 
from the subway. 
</P>
<P>
A three-night program includes accommodations, three breakfasts, one dinner, a 
Washington-by-night tour (viewing Capitol Hill, the Kennedy Center and 
Georgetown) and a day tour that includes visits to the Library of Congress and 
the Supreme Court. Cost for a single is $175; for twin accommodations it's $155 
per person. 
</P>
<P>
The "Ys Way" program also operates a special student courtesy desk in the 
arrivals hall at Kennedy Airport in New York City. The staff provides 
transportation and reservation information for foreign visitors. 
</P>
<P>
Free copies of the "Ys Way" catalogue, which lists international facilities, 
youth travel services and reservation information, are available by contacting 
The Ys Way International, 359 West 34th St., New York 10001, or call (212) 
760-5869. Include a self-addressed, stamped (65 cents postage) envelope. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Bangkok's colorful floating market is one of the most popular 
attractions for visitors to Thailand. ; Photo, Jefferson Memorial lures many 
travelers in Washington, D.C. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
