<P>
CHINA PROPAGANDA? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The blood hasn't dried on Tian An Men Square and you already beat the drum for 
renewed tourist trade for China ("In Wake of Turmoil, China Still Holds 
Surprises," July 16). Elizabeth Mehren's thinly disguised propaganda is not far 
from disgusting. I know Guangzhou, which is, to put it mildly, an unremarkable 
