JUST RELEASED IN PAPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FICTION 
</P>
<P>
THE CARDINAL OF THE KREMLIN by Tom Clancy (Berkley: $5.95). Jack Ryan's current 
mission in the protracted conflict between the superpowers is to rescue an 
American mole in Russia. 
</P>
<P>
ONLY CHILDREN by Rafael Yglesias (Ballantine: $4.50). Two yuppie couples 
encounter the challenges of child-rearing. 
</P>
<P>
THE PENGUIN BOOK OF MODERN BRITISH SHORT STORIES, edited by Malcolm Bradbury 
(Penguin: $7.95). Thirty-four examples of the genre written since 1945 by 
England's most acclaimed authors. 
</P>
<P>
THE NATIONALISTS by William Stuart Long (Dell: $4.95). Continuation of an epic 
tale for Australia's struggle for sovereignty. 
</P>
<P>
THE BRIDE by Julie Garwood (Pocket: $4.50). In an arrangement designed to 
mitigate the hostilities between their two countries, an arrogant Scotsman 
meets his match in his English bride. 
</P>
<P>
NONFICTION 
</P>
<P>
DREAMS OF LOVE AND FATEFUL ENCOUNTERS: The Power of Romantic Passion by Ethel 
S. Person (Penguin: $8.95). Psychoanalyst emphasizes the positive, 
transformational powers of love. 
</P>
<P>
LIKE LIONS THEY FOUGHT by Robert B. Edgerton (Ballantine: $8.95). Critical 1879 
battle between Zulu warriors and the British that ushered in the system of 
apartheid. 
</P>
<P>
RETAKES: Behind the Scenes of 500 Classic Movies by John Eastman (Ballantine: 
$4.95). Eastman's use of film biographies, memoirs and other sources reveals 
unusual backgrounds to films now on video cassette. 
</P>
<P>
VEECK . . . As in Wreck by Bill Veeck with Ed Linn (Fireside: $9.95). Eccentric 
baseball owner -- who unabashedly used every trick in the book to fill a 
ballpark -- writes his autobiography. 
</P>
<P>
PERFECT VICTIM by Christine McGuire and Carla Norton (Dell: $4.95). Account of 
the seven-year abduction, forced submission, and brainwashing of a young woman 
by a man and his wife. 
</P>
<P>
SELF-HELP / REFERENCE 
</P>
<P>
THE RIGHTS OF PATIENTS by George J. Annas JD, MPH (Southern Illinois University 
Press: $8.95). Answers to legal questions about hospital stays and out-patient 
care. 
</P>
<P>
WATERSHEDS by Robert H. Lauer Ph.D. and Jeanette C. Lauer Ph.D. (Ivy: $3.95). 
How to change the direction of undesirable events toward more positive ends. 
</P>
