<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN SHOT DURING ARGUMENT IN PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was in critical condition Saturday night after he was shot during an 
argument in Balboa Park, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Bruce E. Miller, 25, was being held for questioning late Saturday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
According to Lt. Lee Staley, Miller and Sefo Ione, age unknown, became involved 
in an argument at Park Boulevard and Presidents Way about 7:40 p.m. Miller 
allegedly pulled a pistol from his pocket and fired two or three shots at Ione, 
striking him in the arm and leg, Staley said. The assailant then fled. 
</P>
<P>
Miller was stopped at 10th Avenue and Ash Street downtown by police who had 
heard a radio description of the suspect, Staley said. He added that Miller was 
carrying a pistol when he was stopped. 
</P>
<P>
"We don't know yet if he'll be booked on attempted murder or assault with a 
deadly weapon," he said. "We don't yet know the motive." 
</P>
<P>
Ione was taken to UC San Diego Medical Center, where he was in surgery in 
critical condition, according to a hospital spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
