<HEADLINE>
<P>
WISNIEWSKI SIGNS CONTRACT, WORKS OUT WITH RAIDERS; KELLEY AND LILJA RELEASED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OXNARD 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Raiders have released two veterans to make room on the roster for rookies, 
including second-round draft choice Steve Wisniewski. 
</P>
<P>
Veteran free-agent quarterback Mike Kelley was cut to make room for Wisniewski, 
and center George Lilja was dropped Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Wisniewski, an offensive lineman from Penn State taken with the 29th pick, 
signed Saturday morning and participated in two practices after missing the 
first day of two-a-day workouts. 
</P>
<P>
"I wasn't much of a holdout," Wisniewski said. "I ran my 40-yard test before 
camp, I went downtown to take my physical before I came here, and I was staying 
at the team hotel (in El Segundo)." 
</P>
<P>
The Raiders began camp with only six draft choices, two of whom were sent to 
Cedars-Sinai Medical Center for tests. 
</P>
<P>
Wide receiver Gary Gooden of Indiana suffered a knee injury in practice Friday, 
while defensive lineman Charles Jackson from Jackson State has a nagging 
shoulder injury. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
