<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
GARRISON, SHRIVER WIN TO REACH HALL OF FAME TOURNAMENT FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zina Garrison and Pam Shriver, gold-medal winners in the doubles at last year's 
Olympic Games, will face each other in today's final of the Hall of Fame 
Championships at Newport, R.I. 
</P>
<P>
Shriver, seeded second, needed a third-set tiebreaker to defeat Ros Fairbank, 
3-6, 6-3, 7-6 (7-5), Saturday. The top-seeded Garrison defeated No. 8 Gigi 
Fernandez, 6-4, 6-3, in the other semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
Shriver, ranked 10th in the world, hit two backhand volleys for winners in the 
tiebreaker and then played the winning point exactly as she had planned. 
</P>
<P>
"I had one play in mind," she said. "I wanted to have a nice chip backhand and 
follow it, make her hit a volley. It worked to perfection." 
</P>
<P>
Fairbank netted Shriver's chip shot to lose her fourth semifinal singles match 
at Newport. 
</P>
<P>
The South African native, ranked 30th, had three match points in the second 
set. Fairbank netted two returns, and Shriver made a passing shot to stave off 
defeat. 
</P>
<P>
"She came up with the shots when she needed them," Fairbank said. "I played 
well, I was selecting the right shots, but I was not executing them." 
</P>
<P>
Scott Davis upset No. 1-seeded Dan Goldie, 3-6, 6-4, 6-1, in the semifinals of 
the $200,000 OTB International tennis tournament at Schenectady, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
Davis, seeded fourth, will face Simon Youl of Tasmania in today's final. Youl 
defeated Glenn Michibata of Canada, 3-6, 7-6, 7-6. 
</P>
<P>
Goldie dominated the first set against Davis, using his serve-and-volley game 
to keep him off balance. But Davis rallied in the next two sets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
