<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRAPPED MINER EATS OWN SHIRT TO SURVIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CEBU CITY, Philippines 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Workers rescued a copper miner who survived by eating his shirt while trapped 
12 days in a tunnel by a mudslide, a mining company said. 
</P>
<P>
Atlas Consolidated Mining &amp; Development Corp. said in a statement that 
Roberto Lingao-Lingao was rescued Friday. He survived by eating his shirt a 
little at a time and sleeping to conserve energy as fellow miners inched their 
way 1,473 feet through mud and other debris to reach him, the statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
