<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAND OPENINGS; 
</P>
<P>
150 HOMES FOR SALE IN 9 NEIGHBORHOODS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than five years of planning and development is being capped today as 150 
homes in nine different neighborhoods go up for sale in the 4,000-acre Moreno 
Valley Ranch. 
</P>
<P>
The smallest homes have three bedrooms, two bathrooms, about 1,500 square feet 
of living space and start at about $135,000. The largest homes have about 2,500 
square feet, five bedrooms and three baths. 
</P>
<P>
All of the homes have either Spanish Colonial or Spanish Monterey designs. The 
development will have 7,500 homes when it is completed in about five years. 
</P>
<P>
The project has a 27-hole golf course designed by Peter Dye and a 35-acre lake 
for boating and fishing. It also has a large clubhouse, Olympic-size swimming 
pool and many other recreational amenities. 
</P>
<P>
Several schools and a day-care center are also under construction on the site, 
which is being masterdeveloped by Warmington Co. of Costa Mesa. More than 1,700 
acres have been set aside as parks or other open space. 
</P>
<P>
Most of the development is open from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m., although some of the 
builders keep other hours. The project can be reached from the southbound 
Perris Boulevard exit of California 60. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura Development Has 45 2-Story Homes 
</P>
<P>
Silver Valley, a 45-unit residential development, has opened at 5684 Silver 
Valley Ave. in Agoura. 
</P>
<P>
The project, developed by Haseko-Stone, offers two-story, single-family homes 
with four or five bedrooms and three or four baths, ranging in size from 2,870 
to 3,364 square feet. 
</P>
<P>
The homes, which sell from $445,000 to $560,000, have been designed in a 
Spanish architectural style with red tile roofs and textured stucco. 
</P>
<P>
The interiors have vaulted ceilings, soaring pillars, fireplaces, sun decks and 
in some models, a winding staircase. 
</P>
<P>
Three models are available for inspection Saturday through Thursday, noon to 5 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Seagate Colony Models Open for Viewing 
</P>
<P>
Six fully furnished models with one- and two-bedroom floor plans are open for 
viewing at Seagate Colony, a 416-unit townhouse development in Aliso Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
The 27 homes for sale in phase 1 range in size from 606 to 1,125 square feet 
and are priced at $120,900 to $166,900. Monthly dues are $173. 
</P>
<P>
The project is being built by Kathryn G. Thompson Development Co. and move-ins 
are expected in November. The models are open from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. daily at 4 
Jaeger Lane, reached from the California 133 exit of Interstate 5. 
</P>
<P>
61 Homes Now Open at Site in Mira Mesa 
</P>
<P>
The grand opening of Fieldstone Classics features 19 of 61 single-family homes 
being built in Mira Mesa by Fieldstone Classics. 
</P>
<P>
The two-story dwellings, ranging in price from $213,990 to $221,990, were 
designed by Hales-Langston of Orange in a California contemporary style with 
red tile roofs, vaulted ceilings and arched doorways. 
</P>
<P>
The four-bedroom homes feature an optional loft or bonus room and 2 1/2 to 3 
baths. Two plans are offered with two-car garages and range from 1,781 to 1,895 
square feet. 
</P>
<P>
The project, with sales offices at Blakstad Court and Penara Street in Mira 
Mesa, is open daily, except Thursday. 
</P>
