<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMERCIAL SCENE; 
</P>
<P>
BUSINESS CENTER BEING BUILT ON 14-ACRE SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
University Business Center, a $20-million retail and industrial complex, is 
being constructed on a 14-acre site in the East San Gabriel Valley bounded by 
Valley Boulevard on the west, Temple Avenue to the south and Pomona Boulevard 
on the east. 
</P>
<P>
Cordova Chase Co., headquartered in City of Industry, is the developer and the 
Irvine-based Breton Construction Co. is the general contractor. 
</P>
<P>
The site will contain two projects, the 204,000-square-foot University Business 
Center and the University Plaza, a four-building commercial complex fronting on 
Temple Avenue. A new public street, University Parkway, also is being built as 
part of Cordova Chase Co.'s development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
